1 March 2021 The Government Communication and Information System invites you to Africa’s Webinar on COVID-19 that will reflect on the emergence of new Coronavirus variants and their impact on economic recovery taking place on Wednesday, 3 March 2021 at 13h00 CAT. The aim of the event is to create a platform for the World Health Organisation, African Union and the media to exchange latest developments on COVID-19. The Webinar will address the measures taken by various countries to achieve inclusive growth following the economic devastation caused by COVID-19. The speakers for the Webinar are: Ms. Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane, Minister of Tourism in South Africa. Dr. Matshidiso Moeti- World Health Organisation, Regional Head for Africa. Dr. John Nkengasong - African Union Director of the Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention. Dr. Mmboneni Muofhe - The Deputy Director-General (DDG) for Technology Innovation at the Department of Science and Technology in South Africa. Moderator- Ms. Eleni Giokos - CNN Correspondent. We kindly invite you to participate in this important webinar. The details are as follows: Date:            Wednesday, 3 March 2021From:            13h00 – 16h00 CAT Zoom link: https://gcis.zoom.us/j/95365407140?pwd=dTlZajE3Ym96UVlZcmJzRFIyaUhDUT09(link is external) RSVP: Mpho Sekgaphola 0796052659 Email: mphop@gcis.gov.za(link sends e-mail) Enquiries: Mr Ayanda HollowCell: 061488 0634Email: holo@gcis.gov.za(link sends e-mail) Mmemme MogotsiCell: 072 856 4288 Email: mmemme@gcis.gov.za Issued by: Government Communication and Information System